Basta has well made, fresh food and good service. They are consistent and predictable.  For a good restaurant, why 4 stars? Several reasons: the service, the lack of specials, and the relative cost. The service always has flaws. Last night the forgot my drink twice and my wife's wine refill once. Our waitress had a hard time describing the crab pasta I ordered. Not huge misses, but not 5 stars either. The second issue is specials, particularly since the main menu has really changed in the last 2 years. If you are charging $20 to $30 an entree, I expect 3 entree specials for the weekend. There was one lamb special and a special pizza (as there is a wood-fired oven and pizza menu section). Again 4 stars. The last issue is the cost of the secondary items. A calamari appetizer for $12, ok, but bread for the table at $10?!!? Desserts at $8 to $10 each. Those things have to either wow at that price or be several dollars cheaper. If you are dropping by to have a glass of wine and an entree, fine. If you like multiple courses, there are more appropriate choices in Iowa City.

caption: I really enjoy the food at Basta, but recently the service has gotten poor. First of all, they take an EXTREMELY long time to bring out to-go orders (I have waited for nearly 20 minutes on multiple occasions, even though they said my food would be ready at the time I arrived). Today, we picked up a to-go order only to realize when we got home that they forgot all the meat in our meals. When I called to explain and ask for a correction the woman at the front desk was very rude. She insisted that she had not made a mistake with our order, saying that my boyfriend had misspoken when placing the order over the phone. However, he placed the order on speaker phone with me in the room and I heard him list our meals correctly. I asked to speak to her manager and she then left me on hold for several minutes, until someone else finally picked up and asked what I needed help with. I was never allowed to speak to her manager, and no one apologized for the mistake on our order even though we had to drive all the way back to the restaurant to pick up the fixed meals. I used to eat at Basta very regularly, but after this experience I will not be doing so. I expect better service at a restaurant of this caliber with these prices - or at least an apology.

Consistently top notch service, food, and drinks. Atmosphere is traditional and casual with modern trimmings, soft lighting and a candle at each table. Seating can be a little close on busier nights. Service is prompt, courteous, professional and performed with a smile. The food is impeccable from the appetizers to dessert. Menu seems to be seasonal as ingredients are very fresh. Their flatbread appears to be the most popular dish, but I've always had phenomenal pasta and Italian dishes. This is one of Iowa City's priciest restaurants, but is very affordable relative to the quality and quantity of meals. I always go home with leftovers. Rotating taps of 6-7 craft brews, usually about half local. Extensive wine list and creative and tasty cocktails. High end liquor available. Liquor is priced high- it is meant to augment the meal here, not as an intoxicant. For those more inclined towards fun, happy hour taps are half off. Overall I've been impressed with both the food and service every time I go to Basta. I would recommend to anybody wanting an authentic Iowa City experience.
